The paper proposes a deep learning framework for multi-task multi-view learning, which involves both computer vision (image and video) and natural language processing (text) modalities. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely categories. Additionally, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category as the paper deals with multiple modalities. The paper also discusses web classification, which involves text data, suggesting cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another possible category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of correlation coefficients, which is a common technique in information retrieval, suggesting cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible category.
